# E-Commerce Platform — Critical Bug Fixes & Feature Implementation

This plan addresses all 10 issues: bug fixes across admin/storefront data sync, checkout, auth, input focus, dashboard metrics, UI contrast, product creation, auto-refresh; plus new Lead Tracking and Session Recording systems.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Google OAuth**: You must enable Google Sign-In in your Firebase Console (`Authentication → Sign-in method → Google → Enable`). I'll write the code, but it won't work until the provider is enabled in Firebase.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **MongoDB Atlas**: For session recording storage (Issue #10) and behavioral tracking (Issue #9), you'll need to provide a MongoDB connection string. Since this is a **Next.js frontend-only app** (no custom API routes yet), I'll create **Next.js API routes** (`/api/sessions`, `/api/tracking`) that connect to MongoDB from the server side. Please confirm your MongoDB Atlas connection string, or I can set up a placeholder you fill in later.

> [!WARNING]
> **Facebook CDN for images**: The request mentions storing product images on "Facebook CDN". Facebook does not offer a public CDN for arbitrary image hosting. For now, I'll implement image upload via **URL input** (paste any hosted image URL — Facebook post images, Imgur, etc.) and store the URL in Firestore. If you have a specific image hosting workflow, please clarify.

> [!WARNING]
> **rrweb library size**: rrweb adds ~80KB gzipped to the client bundle. With MongoDB Free Tier's 512MB limit, continuous recording for all visitors will fill storage quickly. I'll implement the 30-day auto-purge as requested.

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> 1. **MongoDB Connection String**: Please provide your MongoDB Atlas connection string (format: `mongodb+srv://user:pass@cluster.mongodb.net/dbname`). I'll store it in `.env.local`.
> 2. **Canvas Fingerprinting**: This technique is increasingly blocked by browsers and has privacy/legal concerns (GDPR). Shall I proceed with it, or use a more reliable approach like `FingerprintJS` (open-source, more accurate, less legally risky)?
> 3. **Payment Integration**: You mention fixing checkout but only have COD, bKash, and Nagad. bKash/Nagad are already in the UI — should I implement actual payment gateway integration, or just ensure the existing payment method selection works correctly with order processing?

