## Proposed Changes

The work is organized into 8 phases, ordered by dependency (foundational fixes first, new features last).

---

### Phase 1: Fix Admin Input Focus Loss (Issues #4, #7)

**Root Cause**: The `setForm({...form, field: value})` pattern creates a new object on every keystroke. Combined with `useEffect` hooks that depend on `form.name` (line 21 in `new/page.tsx`), this triggers re-renders that steal focus.

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/admin/products/new/page.tsx)
- Replace `useEffect` that auto-generates SKU/slug on `form.name` change — this is the primary culprit causing re-renders
- Use `useRef` for the form state to prevent unnecessary re-renders, or use `useCallback` with stable references
- Use a debounced approach: only generate SKU/slug on blur, not on every keystroke
- Ensure the `Field` component is defined **outside** the render function (it's currently inline, causing remounts)

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/admin/operations/suppliers/page.tsx)
- Same pattern fix for supplier form inputs in modal

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/admin/operations/accounting/page.tsx)
- Same pattern fix for accounting form inputs in modal

**All admin pages with forms**: Extract the `Field` component to a shared component file. Use `useCallback` for form change handlers to maintain stable references.

---

### Phase 2: Fix Checkout Redirect & Payment System (Issue #2)

**Root Cause**: Line 91-94 in checkout `page.tsx`:
```tsx
if (items.length === 0 && step !== 3) {
  router.push('/cart');
  return null;
}
```
The `useCart` hook's `items` starts as `[]` and is populated asynchronously. On first render, `items.length === 0` is true → immediate redirect before cart data loads.

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/%28storefront%29/checkout/page.tsx)
- Wait for cart `loaded` state before checking items (the hook already exposes `loaded`)
- Change the guard to: `if (loaded && items.length === 0 && step !== 3)`
- Payment methods are already in the UI (COD, bKash, Nagad) — ensure they save correctly to orders
- Add bank transfer option based on client's `paymentSettings`
- Only show payment methods that the admin has enabled

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/admin/operations/settings/page.tsx) *(if exists)*
- Ensure admin can manage payment method settings (enable/disable bKash, Nagad, etc.)
- These settings are already in the `Client.paymentSettings` type

---

### Phase 3: Fix Auto-Refresh Problem (Issue #8)

**Root Cause**: `seedData()` is called on every mount of both `StorefrontLayout` (line 24) and `AdminLayout` (line 53). Since `seedData()` calls `storage.getClients()` which hits Firestore, and the check `if (clients.length > 0) return` still makes a read, this causes unnecessary API calls on every navigation.

#### [MODIFY] [layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/%28storefront%29/layout.tsx)
- Remove `seedData()` call from storefront layout — seed should only run from admin
- Add a localStorage flag `data_seeded` to prevent re-running seed on every mount

#### [MODIFY] [layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/admin/layout.tsx)
- Gate `seedData()` behind a localStorage check: only call if `data_seeded` flag is not set
- After successful seed, set the flag

#### [MODIFY] [seed.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/lib/seed.ts)
- Add localStorage flag after seeding completes
- This prevents the Firestore read on every page navigation

#### All pages with `useEffect(() => { load(); }, [client])`:
- Review all admin pages — the `load` pattern is fine (loads once on mount), but ensure no `setInterval` or polling exists
- Remove any `window.addEventListener('focus', ...)` auto-refresh patterns if present

---

### Phase 4: Client-Admin Data Synchronization (Issue #1)

**Root Cause Analysis**: Both storefront and admin already read from the same Firestore database. The "disconnect" is likely because:
1. Storefront uses `storage.getCartClientId()` to get the client ID, but this may not match the logged-in admin's client
2. After admin makes changes, storefront doesn't refetch (no real-time listeners)
3. The storefront config `storefrontConfig/default` document needs to be set to the admin's client ID

#### [MODIFY] [seed.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/lib/seed.ts)
- Ensure `storage.setCartClientId(cid)` is called during seeding (already done on line 118 ✓)

#### [MODIFY] [layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/admin/layout.tsx)
- After admin login, ensure the storefront client ID is set to the admin's client ID
- Add `storage.setCartClientId(client.id)` in the admin layout effect

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/%28storefront%29/page.tsx)
- Ensure storefront fetches products fresh (no caching issues)
- Products added via admin should appear immediately on storefront refresh

#### [NEW] [useFirestoreListener.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/hooks/useFirestoreListener.ts)
- Create a hook using Firestore `onSnapshot` for real-time listeners
- Use on critical pages (admin dashboard, storefront products) so changes propagate instantly
- This provides true bidirectional sync without polling

