### Phase 9: Session Recording System (Issue #10)

#### Install dependencies:
```bash
npm install rrweb rrweb-player mongodb
npm install -D @types/rrweb @types/rrweb-player
```

#### [NEW] [mongodb.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/lib/mongodb.ts)
- MongoDB client singleton (server-side only)
- Connection to MongoDB Atlas using connection string from `.env.local`

#### [NEW] [useSessionRecorder.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/hooks/useSessionRecorder.ts)
- Initialize rrweb `record()` on storefront mount
- Buffer events and send to API route in batches (every 10 seconds or 100 events)
- Link recording to user/lead ID from fingerprinting
- Stop recording on page unload (use `beforeunload` + `sendBeacon`)

#### [NEW] [api/sessions/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/api/sessions/route.ts)
- POST: Receive session events, store in MongoDB `sessions` collection
- GET: Retrieve sessions for admin playback (with pagination)
- DELETE: Auto-purge sessions older than 30 days
- Document structure: `{ userId, fingerprintId, timestamp, duration, events[], pageViews[], device, browser }`

#### [NEW] [api/sessions/[id]/route.ts](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/api/sessions/[id]/route.ts)
- GET: Retrieve a single session's full event data for playback

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/admin/customers/sessions/page.tsx)
- Replace placeholder session viewer with rrweb-player
- Fetch sessions from MongoDB API route instead of from Firestore leads
- Add session metadata display (duration, pages, device, browser)
- Add pagination and filtering by user/date
- Show all sessions grouped by user identity (deduplication)

#### [MODIFY] [layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/User/Downloads/antigravity/ecommerce-platform/app/%28storefront%29/layout.tsx)
- Integrate `useSessionRecorder` hook to auto-record all storefront sessions

